	<h2><i class="fa fa-scroll"></i><%= application.name %> Principles</h2>
	<p>The <%= application.name %> applications are free to use, but more importantly, you can download the code in order to <a href="#features/self-hostable">set up your own personal cloud</a> on your own server. <%= application.name %> is founded upon the following five principles:</p>

	<div class="well">
		<h2 class="center aligned">Principles</h2>
		<ol>
			<li>
				<h3>Control</h3>
				<p>You should have control over the platform that you use to manage your own data. </p>
			</li>

			<li>
				<h3>Decentralization</h3>
				<p>The essential platforms that you use to manage your data should not be controlled by a handful of tech giants. It's not good for you, the economy, or society. </p>
			</li>

			<li>
				<h3>Sharing</h3>
				<p>The aspect of sharing is so essential that it should be seamlessly integrated into each of your applications instead of tacked on as an afterthought. </p>
			</li>

			<li>
				<h3>User Experience</h3>
				<p>The user experience of using a cloud application should be as good as or better than your desktop experience. </p>
			</li>

			<li>
				<h3>Personalization</h3>
				<p>You should be able to customize your cloud experience to suit your needs and your personal style. </p>
			</li>
		</ol>
	</div>

